For purposes of this section, the following definitions shall apply:
"Cafeteria plan" shall mean a flexible benefits plan which meets the requirements of Section 125 of the Federal Internal Revenue Code;
"Employee" shall mean a person, including an elected public official, who is regularly employed by any department, board, agency, or branch of state government, and who is a contributing member to any one (1) of the retirement systems administered by the state;
"Cabinet" shall mean the Personnel Cabinet;
"Change in family status" shall have the same meaning as used in Section 125 of the Internal Revenue Code and regulations promulgated thereunder; and
"Salary reduction contribution" means all employer contributions that are excludable from gross income under the Internal Revenue Code.

Options available under the plan may include, but are not limited to:
Health insurance coverage;
Managed health care coverage;
Catastrophic illness coverage;
Dental insurance;
Term life insurance-accidental, death, or dismemberment;
Vision insurance;
Long term disability insurance;
Long term medical care; and
Any other benefits which may be offered under the provisions of the Internal Revenue Code and which the cabinet determines to be in the best interests of state employees.
